It is a sigh of relief for students at Mureru primary school in Kieni constituency Nyeri county, the school that had been condemned and was to be closed by Monday, has now been given a new lease of life, after parents united in constructing five classrooms to guarantee their children a stay in school. Kieni MP Kanini Kega has however faulted the method used in allocating NG?CDF funds, citing that deserving constituencies are disadvantaged.